sequenceDiagram
    participant User as External User
    participant Route as OpenShift Route<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Service as {cr-name}-tls Service<br/>443/TCP
    participant OAuth as oauth-proxy<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS TLS1.2+
    participant TrustyAI as trustyai-service<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    participant PVC as PersistentVolume<br/>Filesystem

    Note over User,PVC: Flow 1: User Access to TrustyAI Service

    User->>Route: HTTPS Request<br/>443/TCP, TLS 1.2+
    Route->>Service: TLS Passthrough<br/>443/TCP
    Service->>OAuth: Forward to Pod<br/>8443/TCP HTTPS
    OAuth->>OAuth: Validate OAuth Token<br/>OpenShift SubjectAccessReview
    OAuth->>TrustyAI: Forward (localhost)<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    TrustyAI-->>OAuth: Response
    OAuth-->>Service: HTTPS Response
    Service-->>Route: Response
    Route-->>User: HTTPS Response

    Note over User,PVC: ---

    participant Prometheus as Prometheus
    participant SvcInternal as {cr-name} Service<br/>80/TCP

    Note over Prometheus,PVC: Flow 2: Prometheus Metrics Collection

    Prometheus->>SvcInternal: HTTP GET /q/metrics<br/>80/TCP HTTP
    SvcInternal->>TrustyAI: Forward to Pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    TrustyAI-->>SvcInternal: Metrics (trustyai_spd, trustyai_dir)
    SvcInternal-->>Prometheus: Metrics Response

    Note over Prometheus,PVC: ---

    participant InferenceService as KServe Predictor<br/>InferenceService Pod
    participant TrustyAISvc as TrustyAI Service<br/>{cr-name}:80

    Note over InferenceService,PVC: Flow 3: KServe Payload Logging

    InferenceService->>TrustyAISvc: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>80/TCP HTTP<br/>Payload: prediction data
    TrustyAISvc->>TrustyAI: Forward to Pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    TrustyAI->>PVC: Write payload data<br/>Filesystem
    PVC-->>TrustyAI: Write complete
    TrustyAI-->>TrustyAISvc: HTTP 200 OK
    TrustyAISvc-->>InferenceService: Response

    Note over InferenceService,PVC: ---

    participant ModelMeshPod as ModelMesh Pod<br/>MM_PAYLOAD_PROCESSORS

    Note over ModelMeshPod,PVC: Flow 4: ModelMesh Payload Logging

    ModelMeshPod->>TrustyAISvc: POST /consumer/kserve/v2<br/>80/TCP HTTP<br/>Payload: prediction data
    TrustyAISvc->>TrustyAI: Forward to Pod<br/>8080/TCP HTTP
    TrustyAI->>PVC: Write payload data<br/>Filesystem
    PVC-->>TrustyAI: Write complete
    TrustyAI-->>TrustyAISvc: HTTP 200 OK
    TrustyAISvc-->>ModelMeshPod: Response

    Note over ModelMeshPod,PVC: ---

    participant ControllerMgr as controller-manager
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS
    participant Resources as Deployment, Service,<br/>Route, PVC, ServiceMonitor

    Note over ControllerMgr,Resources: Flow 5: Operator Reconciliation

    ControllerMgr->>K8sAPI: Watch TrustyAIService CRs<br/>HTTPS, TLS 1.2+<br/>Auth: ServiceAccount Token
    K8sAPI-->>ControllerMgr: Event: TrustyAIService Created
    ControllerMgr->>K8sAPI: Create Resources<br/>RBAC: manager-role permissions
    K8sAPI->>Resources: Create Deployment, Service,<br/>Route, PVC, ServiceMonitor
    Resources-->>K8sAPI: Created
    K8sAPI-->>ControllerMgr: Success
    ControllerMgr->>K8sAPI: Update CR Status<br/>phase, ready, conditions
    K8sAPI-->>ControllerMgr: Updated
